JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa posted a R12 billion ($894 million) trade surplus in December, beating market expectations by far, following a revised R1.7 billion deficit in November, data from the revenue agency showed on Tuesday.Exports fell by 6.1% on a month-on-month basis, while imports were down 19.6%, the South African Revenue Service said in a statement.Analysts polled by Reuters had expected a trade surplus of R6 billion for December. ($1 = R13.4700) 